The paper deals with the problem of estimating the edit distance to monotonicity in a sliding window over a data stream. This problem involves data structures and algorithms for processing data streams, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the space complexity of the algorithms, which is related to information theory and falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also uses probabilistic algorithms and discusses their performance, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with partial ordered sets, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the problem of out-of-order streams, which is related to sorting and falls under the category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
